      "content": "i hear you, but i'm worried that \"neat\" might be interpreted differently by the senior partners. like, if they're used to seeing very sleek, straight hair or very standard Western styles, they might see more textured or cultural styles as less \"serious\" or even \"unpolished.\" how can these associates specifically navigate that perception? maybe there are certain ways to style their hair or wrap their hijabs that feel a bit more aligned with that high-level executive aesthetic so they don't get overlooked?",
